comments: Sasser (DET) steals the ball away from Grant (POR) and the ensuing contact is incidental.
Thompson (DET) moves laterally into Grant's (POR) path and initiates body contact that affects Grant's SQBR during the drive.
Thybulle (POR) and Cunningham (DET) come together in the backcourt and the contact quickly dissolves.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Camara's (POR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Grant (POR) briefly grasps Thompson's (DET) left arm as he releases to receive the entry pass.
Thompson (DET) reaches in and deflects the ball away from Grant (POR) and out of bounds.
Hagans (POR) reaches in as Duren (DET) controls the rebound and the contact is marginal.
Sasser (DET) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Grant (POR) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Grant (POR) trails behind Sasser (DET) in transition and any contact that occurs during his driving shot attempt is marginal.
Thybulle (POR) moves alongside of Ivey's (DET) path and marginal contact occurs when he is beaten to the spot during the drive to the basket.
Duren (DET) jumps for the rebound and put-back shot attempt and does not dislodge Walker (POR) from his position.
Sasser (DET) is drawn into the air and initiates body contact with Grant (POR) that causes him to lose his balance.
Walker (POR) establishes himself in Thompson's (DET) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Camara (POR) extends both hands into Cunningham (DET), speeding him up into an opponent.
Walker (POR) briefly rests his right hand toward Ivey's (DET) side and marginal contact occurs during his upward shooting motion.
